environmentalTechnology.description: The Structure of Management Information for Environmental Technology Inc. SNMP devices

allStatuses.name: allStatuses
allStatuses.description: Summary: same as objects 2-7, separated by semicolons

dutycycle.name: dutycycle
dutycycle.description: Current duty cycle, in percent; --- if none available

statusVars.name: statusVars
statusVars.description: Summary of the status of the unit. Is always 7 characters Character 1 is super-state: govering whole system, if this unit is a master S=slave (not a master) M=master; N=master but system off line D=director; D=director but system off line master: for redundant systems director: for increasing pumping capability Character 2 is major state: N=normal, S=standby, L=leaky Character 3 is environment: N=normal, C=cold, H=hot Character 4 is canister 1 condition: O=OK (ie dry), F=full (wet), U=unknown, D=dead Character 5 is canister 1 usage: I=idle, U=in use, R=regenerating Character 6 is canister 2 condition, as in character 4 Character 7 is canister 2 usage, as in character 5

temperature.name: temperature
temperature.description: Current temperature, in degrees F or C

alarms.name: alarms
alarms.description: Current alarm conditions: is a list of them Each character has a - for no alarm, or an A or W if there is an alarm. A means alarm (serious), W means a warning (not so serious). Severity levels may later change. List of alarms: (later versions may add more): A1: Low pressure A2: High pressure W3: High duty cycle W4: High temperature W5: Low temperature W6: Unused A7: Canister 1 won't heat A8: Canister 1 won't cool A9: Canister 2 won't heat A10: Canister 2 won't cool A11: Unable to pressurize A12: Dew point alarm W13: Compressor timeout (for future use) W14: Communications error A15: Canister 1 thermistor bad A16: Canister 2 thermistor bad A17: Ambient thermistor bad A18: Overpressure A19: Bad calibrations in EEPROM A20: Bad limits in EEPROM A21: Short cycling A22: Pump shut down due to error condition

compressorHours.name: compressorHours
compressorHours.description: Number of hours that the compressor has been running; resolution is tenths of an hour.

majorState.name: majorState
majorState.description: Major state of the dehydrator. Online: currently pressurizing. Standby: not pressurizing. Leaky: shut down because of inability to pressurize.

cycleTime.name: cycleTime
cycleTime.description: Time of last duty cycle in seconds; 0.0 means none available

lowerLimit.name: lowerLimit
lowerLimit.description: The pressure, in PSI or mbar, at which the unit starts to pump

upperLimit.name: upperLimit
upperLimit.description: The pressure, in PSI or mbar, which the unit pressurizes to

lowerAlarmLimit.name: lowerAlarmLimit
lowerAlarmLimit.description: The pressure, in PSI or mbar, below which the unit declares a low pressure alarm

upperAlarmLimit.name: upperAlarmLimit
upperAlarmLimit.description: The pressure, in PSI or mbar, above which the unit declares a high pressure alarm
